				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lute of the Mischiefmaker<a name="65743"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 5 04 9:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I notice that the illusion is usable from inventory, so expect that other classes may bid on this if it drops.</span></blockquote>
<br />
Actually, this won't be something to worry about. The illusion is clickable from the inventory but you must &quot;be able to equip&quot; the item to click it.
<br />

<br />
There are three types of clickies:
<br />
1. Must Equip : must equip to click
<br />
2. Any Slot/Can Equip : can click from inventory by someone who can equip the item
<br />
3. Any Slot : can click from inventory by anyone
<br />

<br />
The lute, according to lucy, is the second type so other classes will not be able to click it.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
